  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Revival After the Great War,\" published in 2021 by Leuven University Press, showcases strong commercial linkage with notable mentions on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, indicating a significant interest in its themes and insights.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Revival After the Great War\" explores the cultural, political, and social transformations following World War I, offering a nuanced understanding of its aftermath. Despite the absence of citations and online discussions, the work demonstrates a notable presence through commercial avenues. It is listed on popular platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, which support its visibility and may contribute to discussions in both academic and broader public contexts.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of formal citations indicates that the academic discourse surrounding this work may still be in its infancy, yet the existing commercial interest suggests that its themes resonate strongly with an audience eager for insights into the post-war world. Such engagement may lead to a gradual build-up of citations as readers delve into its content and integrate its findings into their own research or personal explorations.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Another layer of visibility is provided through the inferred roles related to public knowledge and sustainability. The work's alignment with sustainability goals, evidenced by a count of 1 relevant Sustainable Development Goal (SDG), underscores its potential relevance in ongoing discussions about societal stability and resilience in the wake of conflicts. This aspect may attract interest from scholars and practitioners focused on these critical themes.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Overall, while direct academic discourse metrics are low, the foundation set by \"Revival After the Great War\" through its commercial presence and thematic relevance highlights its potential for future scholarly engagement and cultural dialogue. The work may serve as a stepping stone for further research and discussions around the complex legacies of the Great War in various societal contexts.</p>",
